This paper deals with mechanism design for house allocation, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithms presented in the paper are also based on computational techniques such as polynomial-time algorithms, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the concept of individual rationality, which is a key concept in decision theory and social choice theory, making cs.DS another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the allocation of resources, which is a topic in optimization and algorithm design, making cs.SI a possible sub-category as well.
